    # game/areas/greenmountaintribe2chief.rpy:368
    old "He pierces you with his cold eyes. “‘En speak.” \n\nYou share the sparse information you possess. The possible arrival of the messengers, the negotiations with the settlements, the states of the roads. “If everything goes according to the officials’ plans,” you conclude, “you have no way of stopping the days of merchants and soldiers. I ask you not to change your way of life, but to agree to meet with whoever the city sends here, and to reject them with your words, not violence.” \n\nThe long pause is broken by {color=#f6d6bd}Gaiane{/color}. “[pcname], apologies, but wait outside.” She speaks gently, but with a hint of melancholy. “We need to talk as a chief and a shaman, for t’ tribe’s soul is in danger.” "
