    old "While it turns out that the leaders are quite familiar with {i}spirit rocks{/i}, {color=#f6d6bd}the shaman{/color} is hesitant to judge if they can be used in the way described by {color=#f6d6bd}Photios{/color}. “In t’ tales I carry, t’ strengt’ of pneuma shapes t’ same way t’ muscles of a shell does. ‘Tere were heroes born as weaklings, as ‘tere were ones wit’ little breat’. And ‘tese souls risked ‘teir lives to learn, wondering far and deep, finding sages and amulets. But as ‘tere are no stories of an armless woman who grew to be a hunter, ‘tere are also none of a spell-less man who mastered magic.” "
