    # game/areas/greenmountaintribe2chief.rpy:591
    old "“What good could it bring us?” {color=#f6d6bd}The chief{/color} leans back, as if there’s nothing to talk about. After a few breaths, {color=#f6d6bd}the shaman{/color} chips in. \n\n“We’ll enter t’ island like a traveler returning to ‘eir bed. Eyes of t’ cityfolk see not our homeland, but ‘eir failed search for iron. Eyes of t’ ot’er tribes see our lost treasure not as our soil, sky, and rains, but only as belongings to grab and sell. Our friends help us keep an eye on t’ island, and if anyone breaks our rule, we’ll be ready to swim ‘tere, and stop ‘eir greed. But it’s no longer a home to any human soul.” "
